USE university_health_clinic;

VALUES ('Anesthesiology', 'Anesthesiology involves administering anesthetics to patients to block pain and facilitate medical procedures. Anesthesiologists monitor patients'' vital signs during procedures to ensure their safety and comfort.');

VALUES ('Cardiology', 'Cardiology is the study and treatment of heart and cardiovascular diseases. Cardiologists diagnose and treat conditions such as heart attacks, arrhythmias, heart failure, and congenital heart defects.');

VALUES ('Dermatology', 'Dermatology deals with the diagnosis and treatment of skin, hair, and nail disorders. Dermatologists treat conditions ranging from acne and psoriasis to skin cancer and perform cosmetic procedures such as Botox injections and laser hair removal.');

VALUES ('Family Medicine', 'Family Medicine is a medical specialty that focuses on comprehensive primary care for individuals and families of all ages, genders, and diseases. Family Medicine physicians provide preventative care, treat acute and chronic illnesses, and coordinate care with other specialists.');

VALUES ('Hematology', 'Hematology is the branch of medicine that deals with the diagnosis and treatment of blood disorders. Hematologists diagnose and treat conditions such as anemia, bleeding disorders, and blood cancers.');

VALUES ('Infectious Disease', 'Infectious Disease specialists diagnose and treat diseases caused by infectious agents such as bacteria, viruses, fungi, and parasites. They also work to prevent the spread of infections in hospitals and communities.');

VALUES ('Nephrology', 'Nephrology is the study and treatment of kidney diseases. Nephrologists diagnose and treat conditions such as kidney stones, chronic kidney disease, and kidney failure.');

VALUES ('Neurology', 'Neurology is the study and treatment of disorders of the nervous system. Neurologists diagnose and treat conditions such as stroke, epilepsy, Parkinson''s disease, and multiple sclerosis.');

VALUES ('Obstetrics and Gynecology', 'Obstetrics and Gynecology is a medical specialty that deals with women''s reproductive health. Obstetricians and Gynecologists provide care for women during pregnancy and childbirth, and diagnose and treat conditions such as endometriosis, infertility, and cervical cancer.');

VALUES ('Oncology', 'Oncology is the study and treatment of cancer. Oncologists diagnose and treat all types of cancer using a variety of treatment modalities including chemotherapy, radiation therapy, and surgery.');













VALUES ('Gastroenterology', 'Gastroenterology is the study and treatment of diseases of the digestive system. Gastroenterologists diagnose and treat conditions such as ulcers, inflammatory bowel disease, and liver disease.');

VALUES ('Geriatrics', 'Geriatrics is the medical specialty that focuses on the health and well-being of older adults. Geriatricians diagnose and treat conditions that are common in older adults, such as dementia and osteoporosis.');

VALUES ('Hematology-Oncology', 'Hematology-Oncology is the combined study and treatment of blood disorders and cancer. Hematology-Oncologists diagnose and treat conditions such as leukemia, lymphoma, and multiple myeloma.');

VALUES ('Infectious Disease Control', 'Infectious Disease Control is the specialty that focuses on the prevention and control of infectious diseases. Infectious Disease Control specialists work to prevent the spread of infectious diseases in hospitals and communities.');

VALUES ('Neonatology', 'Neonatology is the medical specialty that focuses on the care of newborn infants, particularly those who are premature or have health problems. Neonatologists diagnose and treat conditions such as respiratory distress syndrome and jaundice.');

VALUES ('Pain Medicine', 'Pain Medicine is the specialty that focuses on the management of pain, particularly chronic pain. Pain Medicine physicians diagnose and treat conditions that cause pain, and use a variety of techniques to manage pain, including medications and interventional procedures.');

VALUES ('Physical Medicine and Rehabilitation', 'Physical Medicine and Rehabilitation is the specialty that focuses on the management of disabilities and injuries through physical therapy, occupational therapy, and other rehabilitation techniques. Physical Medicine and Rehabilitation physicians diagnose and treat conditions such as spinal cord injuries and stroke.');

VALUES ('Sleep Medicine', 'Sleep Medicine is the specialty that focuses on the diagnosis and treatment of sleep disorders, such as insomnia and sleep apnea. Sleep Medicine physicians may use a variety of techniques to diagnose and treat sleep disorders, including sleep studies and medication.');

VALUES ('Sports Medicine', 'Sports Medicine is the specialty that focuses on the prevention and treatment of injuries related to sports and exercise. Sports Medicine physicians diagnose and treat conditions such as sprains and strains, and work with athletes to prevent injuries and improve performance.');